The paper discusses statistical tests for random number generators, which are commonly used in cryptographic information protection systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper deals with asymptotic estimates and ergodic sources, which are concepts commonly studied in Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses families of tests, which suggests that it may belong to the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper may also belong to the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), as the concept of random number generators is relevant to network security.
